Her bizarre commentary began when she shared a video clip on Instagram of her Chanel handbag as she watched the results on television.

She captioned it: "#besmart pay attention and work hard to buy @chaneloffocial #remain where's Sunderland? Does Sarah Palin live there? Lol."

Throughout the course of the results, the star has continued to share her views on the referendum on social media.

Following Sunderland's decision to leave the EU, she blamed the city for the drop in the pound.

