She tweeted the Independent newspaper: "@Independent why? prove the UK will not trigger anger by allowing (sunderland) to lower the UK pound - THIS IMPACT WILL CONTROL ALL MARGINS."

She added: "good luck with the pound.. will take you about 15 years to get it back up #REMAIN instead."

It appeared that the Mean Girls star was unaware that voting had closed as she continued to list reasons why she thought the UK should remain in the EU.

The 29-year-old shared a link to an article which listed 10 reasons to vote remain in the referendum.

