Nigel Farage, the leader of the United Kingdom Independence Party (UKIP), makes a statement after Britain voted to leave on the European Union

GETTY

As the results rolled in, Lindsay tweeted that she was unsure of where Kettering and Swindon but was quickly informed of their location.

She politely replied that she was thankful for their help: "@BBCBreaking @BBCWorld @BBCNews thank you for explaining where #Sunderland AND #Swindon ARE... #Remain #EUref."

Her latest tweet on the topic read: "#Remain #besmart #onelone #lovenothate #FREETRADE."

It's clear Lindsay is a big supporter of the Remain campaign along with Benedict Cumberbatch, Rita Ora, HelenaBonham Carter and J.K Rowling.

